`.gitignore`.\n- RFC 2119 keywords throughout; singular direction; binding constraints in §0; minimum-implementation framing with reuse primitives named per part.\n- The **operator-UX checklist** is triggered (top-level pages, long job, destructive actions) and committed once for the shared window — including an explicit note that the spec-writer's web hidden-controls treatment has no analogue in this desktop app.\n- Mandatory closing sections present: Acceptance criteria (AC-U1.1…AC-U8.4), Files in scope, Test artifacts, References.\n\n**Three plan-vs-codebase corrections recorded (codebase wins):**\n1. `MaterialPreview.show*` return `Plotly.NET.GenericChart` (via `Analytics/Charting.fs:85` `Chart.Line`) → hosted in **WebView2**, not ScottPlot/AvaPlot as the plan stated.\n2. Committable project files are `<name>.ocproj.json` (`ConstructionPage.fs:225`), not `.ocproj`.\n3. `JobRunner.startBackground` takes only `run`/`onDone` (`JobRunner.fs:127`); progress threads through the run loop — so the root model keeps a **single** fit-state source of truth (`SynthesisFitPage.Model`) instead of the plan's duplicate `JobModel` field.\n\nNo files outside the allowed scope (`.spec-md`, `.history`) were edited.\nDone. I authored `specs/0024/.spec-md` from the operator plan and recorded the cycle in `.history` via the safe writer. Summary of what I produced:\n\n**Spec 0024 — Wire the Optical Constructor MVU core into a live FuncUI app.** An 8-part arc (U1→U8) ordered by priority, with **U1 marked CRITICAL — land first** so the splitter and implementer get the ordering signal:\n\n- **U1** — root Elmish MVU host (`Shell.fs`), rewire `Program.fs` mount, shell switches on panel id, stack panel read-only, **`ui-smoke` gate** + new headless `OpticalConstructor.Ui.Tests` project.\n- **U2** stack editing + async node-solve `Cmd`; **U3** materials; **U4** sources; **U5** chart panel + reusable `ChartHosts.fs` adapters; **U6** results/schematic/workspace; **U7** synthesis/fit + background 